Wash and dry produce.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{1%ounce}, @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, and @Garlic Powder{1%tsp} until combined.

> Be sure to measure the garlic powder—we sent more!

Lay @Sourdough Bread{4%slice} out on a clean work surface.

Spread one side of each bread slice with aioli.

Evenly layer half the bread slices with @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup} and @White Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup}; top with remaining bread slices, aioli sides down, to form sandwiches.

Heat @Butter{2%TBSP} and a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium heat.

Add sandwiches and cook, gently pressing with a #spatula{}, until bread is golden and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side, adding an additional @Butter{1%TBSP} when flipping.

> Work in batches if necessary, adding more butter if needed; lower heat if browning too quickly.

== Balsamic Arugula Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @Balsamic Glaze{2%tsp} and @Olive Oil{2%tsp}; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

> Be sure to measure the balsamic glaze—we sent more!

Add @Arugula{2%ounce} to bowl with vinaigrette; toss to coat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== To Serve ==

Halve sun-dried tomato grilled cheese sandos on a diagonal; divide between plates. Serve with salad on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.